            <h3>What is the method for composting?</h3>
            <p class="mb-4" style="color:black;">
                1. Start collecting compostable material and add it to your pile.<br />
                2. Empty your pail into the pile (or bin) daily. It’s the perfect chore for the kiddos!<br />
                3. Turn your compost pile. Every month or so, grab your pitchfork or a shovel and mix your pile up a bit. This helps speed up the decomposition process, heats up your pile, and keeps away any unwanted pests. <strong>Note</strong>: If you are using a bin, you’ll just turn it inside the bin.               
            </p>
            @*<p class="mb-4"><a href="#" class="readmore">Visit website</a></p>*@
